                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/599.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Nicaragua</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Nicaragua</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1913</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to answer your
                    excellency’s note of October 27 in which you kindly enclosed a copy of the
                    letter sent on October 6 by your excellency to Messrs. Brown Brothers &amp; Co.
                    and J. &amp; W. Seligman &amp; Co., bankers of New York City, in which letter
                    your excellency states that in Nicaraguan matters you have acted and intend in
                    future to act solely in the capacity of adviser; of all of which I take due
                    note.</p>
                <p>I take the liberty of expressing to your excellency on behalf of my Government
                    and for myself our thanks for the inestimable services which your excellency has
                    lent to Nicaragua during the short time you have occupied the high position of
                    Secretary of State of the United States of America.</p>
                <p>With assurances [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Emiliano Chamorro</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
